I cannot believe this year is coming to a close.. SO MANY MEMORIES and accomplishments. Some favorites from this year would be: 

Brad and I traveling alone some for the first time in a long time. The kids are a little older, which is bittersweet but we needed time away more than I even realized. 

Ironically- another favorite from this year is traveling more with the kids!! They are at the ages where you’re like ok- we can DO THIS 😂 I took the 2 older ones to KC with me to a dress meeting, and we made a mini vacay out of it. By far a favorite 2022 memory. 

Olivia’s trip to get her pointe shoes in January and also her first YAGP competition made the favorites. I literally sobbed the entire time watching our “tiny dancer” do her classical piece on stage. So proud of that 9 year old girl. 

I had to add launching my brand to my highlight reel. I still can’t fully believe it. I launched @viebylindsey in March with a spring dress and later our second dress- a holiday one. I am so grateful for all of your love and support!! 

I took a few girls’ trips this year, and one special one was our Nashville trip! I don’t get to see my besties @attaliahstrubel & @misaliddiard all that much (missed you @calydays ) so it was definitely a 2022 highlight.

We took a family beach trip!! Family time is and will always be the quickest way to fill my cup!! 

After 5 years of homeschooling, our kids ALL went to school. So crazy but it’s been so good for them and definitely a family milestone. 

Lastly, we welcomed sweet Dottie into our family. Crazy how you don’t realize what you’re missing until you get a puppy. 🐶 Surprising tbe kids was hands down one of my most favorite memories from 2022!! 

I hope this year was a good one for you. I’m looking forward to what 2023 holds! I truly feel in my heart it will be the best year yet!! 

#happynewyear2022 #2022memories #agegaprelationship #ourcandidmoments #ourfamily #largefamilylife #blendedfamilylife #momlifeunfiltered #realmom #momofmany

Happy New Year!! Each year I get so excited to come up with a new set of goals (I don’t really do resolutions), and sometimes when I feel drawn to a certain word I make it my “word” for the year. 

This year, I’ll be honest- I’m just not feeling a certain word. 2023 will be a year of thoughtfulness and being intentional with our time. A year of doing my very very best not to step foot on the hamster wheel that I found myself on frequently in 2022. I will still be working and creating content- my blog and social media gives me so much freedom to scratch that “need to be creative” itch. 🙃 I will still be working on my @viebylindsey brand and creating new designs. It has been a longtime dream and something I am really really proud of. 

What I won’t be doing is saying “yes” if it’s not something that I believe in, can’t possibly fit on my plate, interferes with my family and the time we can slow down and be together, etc. I know you know what I mean. When you have a lot of kids who also have dreams and passions, things can get crazy if you don’t become intentional and selective with when and how you choose to say your “yes.” 

So- if you need me I will be over here cleaning my plate, protecting my peace, and organizing of course- SO much organizing that I will be sharing soon! 

Some things you can be on tbe lookout for from me in this new year- more family content. It’s your favorite and no matter what direction I go, it’s always so clear- y’all love to see our family! (My hubby swears everyone is here for him 🤣🤭) I will be sharing more of the free monthly capsule that goes out each month and the looks that go with it. I will also be sharing more day to day life, recipes, etc. I’m REALLLLY excited and ready 2023!! What are some things you would like to see me share more of in this new year?!

Man some days are hard but being present with my littles is something I truly cherish. I saw something on the ‘gram the other day that listed deathbed regrets, and the one that stuck with me the most was the one about being present with your kids during their younger years. I won’t be the perfect mom… ever…. but I’ll always do my best and soak up ALLL the moments that I possibly can. ❤️

Baking together is one of those things you hope they always remember 🥰 I picked them up from school and gave them the option of 1) a nature walk outside together or 2) baking together.. they chose baking so we decided to make my hubby’s favorite cookies! 

The way it works for us with 4 of kiddos is taking turns. We go down the recipe list, and each of them get to measure and add things to our dough. Vivi is mostly here to “clean up” the bowl and mixing whisks 😂 

We all agreed that we love these cookies more than our original chocolate chip recipe! You can find both on our blog- themasseyblog.com ✨

#bakingwithlove #bakingwithkids #cookierecipes #ourfamily #homemadecookie

Happy Easter from our family to yours! 

At age 15 I “thought” I was saved. I went to the front at church camp, said the prayer and went back home and was baptized shortly after. I never fully understood what that meant.. until I became pregnant with Olivia. 

A baby was something we had fought so hard for, and it was truly the first time I was faced with something 100% out of my control. Throw in the fact that I worked around radiation and I’m sure you can see where my mind went. Anxiety crept in and some days it was crippling… but Jesus. 😭

There were more days than I could count that He carried me during that pregnancy, and it was during this time that I fully experienced what it meant to put my faith in Him and to trust Him with all that I had. I finally learned what salvation truly meant. 

Easter is a special day, and it’s safe to say I’d be a mess without Him. So grateful today and every day for that empty tomb. ✝️

There’s something about watching each of your littles grow up… but the baby hits me a little differently. Yesterday I just noticed so much how she’s changed this school year… all in good ways but it all just makes her SEEM so much more grown. 

Her voice and our conversations have changed some, she no longer hides behind me at pickup or drop off, she’s become quite the fashionista ☺️, and just the amount of things she knows and has learned blows me away… and also makes me a teensy bit teary-eyed 🥹 

When I was pregnant with Hayes, we didn’t find out his gender because I remember Brad saying “this could be the last one,” and I also remember telling him in Target one day that I just couldn’t talk about it. Even saying we could be done at 3 would steal my joy during that pregnancy. I truly believe that is God’s way of telling you that you’re not “done” with babies. So thankful we listened to Him. Life wouldn’t be the same with our little Pookie Bear 🥰.

Today is our first official day of summer!! This school year has been nothing short of amazing for our entire family, and we were all pretty sad to see it fly by. 

A group of families started getting together to provide a Christ-centered, Charlotte Mason education for our kids 4 years ago. For three years, kids attended a homeschool day at our house where us moms took turns teaching Charlotte Mason lessons, and last August the dream of offering this type of education in the form of a school came to life. 

At our end of year program yesterday, the growth that each of my kids experienced this year was so apparent, and honestly brought me to tears. I can’t speak highly enough of the families, teachers, administrators, that God placed in this little school, and I can’t wait to see what He does in the years to come! 🥹

Happy Mother’s Day to all the amazing mamas out there! And also for those who are still in their season of waiting or grieving  a loss, my thoughts and prayers are with you... I have been there too. You are not forgotten. 🩷 

#happymotherday #raisingmytribe

We had the best weekend watching the girls perform in Swan Lake! It was Vivi’s first time on “the big stage” so we were really proud of her, and getting to see Olivia and all of her friends perform after weeks of hard work was so special too! I definitely shed some tears just seeing it all come together in such a beautiful way. 🥹

✨I’m really focusing on my health right now. I decided that this year would be the year I get back to my healthy weight and work on just living there- and no I don’t have a certain weight in mind. ✨We used to be really good at prioritizing one on one time with each of our kids, and somehow between life and kid activities it’s become harder and harder to maintain. So- we are making it a priority again, and I’m really excited! 

✨We live in a barn home, and I have been meaning to set up some office space in our loft. I even have a desk, chair, and a printer there.. so the goal is to get it all the way done so I have a space for work and not just spread out all over our house. I thrive on structure and organization so this will be a big deal for me. 

✨Get back to carb cycling- I know it’s not for everyone but it has been easy for me in the past to hit goals this way, and I sort of enjoyed it so I’m going to give it a go again for a while and just see what happens.

Soaking all the Prague experiences up that we can!! Today we went to see the Tower of Books at the Municipal Library, found the smallest street in Prague, visited the cutest little gingerbread shop, and took the girls on a old car tour around the city!  It was such a full and exciting day 🥰

Prague/ Day 4:  We toured Troja Chateau, grabbed a yummy lunch, and then later took the girls to Lennon Wall once they got out of class. I still can’t get over the beautiful sights here, and I’m learning the culture a little better.. sort of 😄 🙈

This was yesterday in Prague! I was too exhausted to edit any videos last night but - yesterday consisted of a trip to the Street Market where we grabbed lunch and I had to take a turn in the Love Tester chair (not sure I have laughed this hard in a while 😂), made a stop at the Illusion Museum after we picked up the girls from ballet, and then we HAD to have one of the chimney cakes we kept seeing everyone eating! We went to Good Food Coffee and Bakery, and I got the original crust with Nutella drizzled on the inside and then added vanilla ice cream with whipped topping.. 🤤🤤 so good!

Days 6 / 7 / 8 in Prague! We went on a 3 hour walking tour with the girls on Saturday, spent Sunday at the zoo, and then Monday we had a low key day and found the cutest bistro near our hotel! We also learned the equivalent of door dashing here in Europe and have been frequent flyers of Bolt Food 😂😂😂

Prague Day 9!! This was maybe my favorite day- we toured the astronomical clock tower and got to actually go to the top!! Next we grabbed some yummy meat and cheese trays at a nearby restaurant. It started pouring down rain and hour before we got the girls from ballet so we had to grab some ponchos from a street market (so fashionable 😂). Once we picked them up we headed to the Klementinum library tour. It was so much fun but SO MANY STAIRS!! The view was similar to the clock tower but without the iron bars. We also squeezed in some dinner and desserts at the pastry academy in Prague (IPPA). So much walking but literally the best day!! 🥹
We are leaving Prague and heading to Rome today! This trip has been so much fun, and I’m already mentally planning our first trip back as a family 🥹🥹
One of my most favorite Prague moments… it was raining outside, and I was sitting in the cutest macaron shop with my girl -The Mad Rabbit- taste testing one of every single flavor they had 😂

Crazy to think six pregnancies in six years! I remember that feeling after my first miscarriage, and all the people who I know were well-meaning that kept telling me that maybe it was time to be done since we had two healthy little ones- a boy and a girl… but then I also remember that feeling I just couldn’t shake of “no wait there’s more.” I have always pictured a bigger family and lots of people around our table during the holidays, but after having that miscarriage, I wondered if that was maybe God’s way of gently telling me that it was time to be done. I’m so thankful that I did not listen or lean into that fear. I truly believe that when it’s time, God gives you a peace and  an understanding of that. I’m so glad I didn’t let anyone make that decision for us ❤️

These are my progress pics from my Ultimate Duo treatment! It’s a 2-step treatment that combines radiofrequency microneedling with a CO2 laser treatment. The microneedling takes care of the deeper skin layers while the laser targets the upper layers. I have to say that this is by far the best thing I’ve done for my skin!! I told you guys that one of my major goals for 2024 was to not wear makeup or NEED makeup. This has helped me make so much progress in that area, and my “downtime” was super minimal. I wore Vaseline on my face for the first 48 hours but that was it. Both my skin tone and texture have changed just after one treatment! I’ll be getting my second in about 3 weeks so I’ll keep you  guys posted!
